00:33:27,245 --> 00:33:56,084
before making a statement prior to possible, in a case of possible misconduct by that officer? So we know that they can, the chief detailed how they can review footage prior to a case that's going to court. The DA is asking for that. But has there been a case where an officer is allowed to review footage if there is a case of misconduct? So that's the only question I have. I know Barry has some more. Thank you.

